# Shamiso Page Structure Patterns

Use these conventions for all `src/app/**/page.tsx` pages to keep structure consistent.

- Start with a clear intro block (hero or page header) that states value and intent immediately.
- Follow with logically grouped sections (problem, value, proof, CTA) rather than ad-hoc section ordering.
- Keep CTA strategy consistent: at least one primary CTA above the fold and one near conversion points.
- Reuse existing chrome and patterns from current pages (`Header`, `Footer`, section containers, card groupings).
- Use consistent content width and spacing containers (`max-w-*`, responsive `px-*`, and section `py-*` rhythm).
- Prefer existing interaction patterns (buttons, badges, cards, icon + heading + description blocks).
- Keep metadata complete (`title`, `description`) and aligned with existing SEO tone and keyword strategy.
- If linking partners, prefer centralized link references (`PARTNER_LINKS`) and `PartnerRedirect` where applicable.
- Validate mobile-first responsiveness using existing Tailwind breakpoints.

## Do Not

- Do not invent new page scaffolding patterns when equivalent project patterns already exist.
- Do not bury CTA actions at the bottom only.
- Do not mix conflicting spacing systems within the same page.
